{
  "texts": [
    "The discriminator will not categorize a single picture as either genuine or fake; rather, it will evaluate pairs of images (an input visual and an unidentified visual that is either a target visual or a made visual) and give a real or fake label to each pair of photos.",
    "The loss function is denoted by the expression min G max E x,y [log D(x, G(x))] + E x,y [log(1-D (G (x,y))],and its definition can be found here.",
    "The problem with pix2pix is that it needs the two picture spaces to be pre-formatted into a single X/Y image that comprises both of the pictures that are strongly connected with each other.",
    "Using Pix2pix GAN, satellite photos are translated from one image to another and then converted to Google maps format shown in Fig. 10.",
    "Cycle-GANCycleGAN translates images."
  ]
}